---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import BackLink from "../components/BackLink.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <BackLink href="/" label="Back to home" />

        <!-- HERO -->

        <section class="mb-20 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-10">

            <img
                src="/og-image.png"
                alt="Miguel Ángel Moza Barquilla"
                class="w-80 h-80 rounded-full object-cover border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 shadow-md ring-2 ring-blue-500/20"
            />

            <div>
                <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">About Me</h1>

                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                    I'm Miguel Ángel, a backend developer passionate about
                    software architecture, system evolution and solving complex
                    problems through clean and maintainable code.
                </p>

                <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                    My path into software development was not linear. It was
                    shaped by experiences across hospitality, industrial
                    environments and a growing curiosity about how systems work
                    behind the scenes.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- MY JOURNEY -->

        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">My Journey</h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                Since I was young I always felt drawn to technical subjects and
                scientific thinking. However, the academic path I initially
                chose didn't fully match my interests and I eventually moved
                into the workforce instead of continuing my studies at that
                time.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                For several years I worked in the hospitality sector, an
                environment that requires discipline, teamwork and the ability
                to perform under pressure. These years shaped my work ethic and
                taught me the value of consistency and responsibility.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                Later I transitioned into the industrial sector, working with
                additive manufacturing systems. This experience would
                unexpectedly become the turning point that led me into
                programming.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- DISCOVERING PROGRAMMING -->

        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Discovering Programming</h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                While working with industrial 3D printers I began interacting
                with
                <strong>G-Code</strong>, a command-based language used to
                control manufacturing machines.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                Understanding how sequences of instructions could control
                complex mechanical behaviour fascinated me. I started
                experimenting with small automation macros that simplified
                printing workflows and improved machine operations.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                That curiosity quickly evolved into a deeper interest in
                programming and software systems. After some reflection and
                personal circumstances that forced me to stop working for a
                period of time, I decided to take the opportunity to return to
                education and formally study web development.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- BECOMING A DEVELOPER -->

        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Becoming a Developer</h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                I enrolled in the Web Application Development program (DAW)
                while continuing to work full-time. This period required strong
                discipline and time management, but it confirmed that software
                development was the field I wanted to pursue professionally.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                Since then I have focused my career on backend development,
                working on systems involving integrations, APIs and complex
                business domains in the tourism software industry.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- OUTSIDE TECH -->

        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Outside of Tech</h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                Outside of software development I enjoy activities that help me
                keep a clear mind and maintain balance.
            </p>

            <ul
                class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 list-disc pl-6"
            >
                <li>
                    Cycling — I enjoy long rides that allow me to disconnect and
                    think.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Music — especially punk rock, which has been part of my life
                    for many years.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- MINDSET -->

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-6">
                How I Approach Technology
            </h2>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
                My background outside the software industry shaped how I
                approach technology today. I value systems that are
                understandable, maintainable and designed to evolve as business
                complexity grows.
            </p>

            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                I'm particularly interested in how architectural decisions age
                over time and how backend systems adapt when real-world
                constraints start to shape the design.
            </p>
        </section>
    </article>
</BaseLayout>
